atNtp.name: atNtp

revisions.description: MIB revision history dates in descriptions updated.

atNtp.description: This MIB file contains definitions of managed objects for the Allied Telesis Network Time Protocol configuration.

atNtpPeerIndexNext.name: atNtpPeerIndexNext
atNtpPeerIndexNext.description: This object represents the next available value for the object 'atNtpPeerIndex'. For creation of a new entry in the 'atNtpPeerTable', a management application should read this object, get the value and use the same.

atNtpPeerTable.name: atNtpPeerTable
atNtpPeerTable.description: This table contains information on the Network Time Protocol (NTP) peers' configurations in the system.

atNtpPeerIndex.name: atNtpPeerIndex
atNtpPeerIndex.description: This object represents the index corresponding to a particular NTP server or peer configuration in the system. For creation of a new entry, the value of this object should be same as that of the value of 'atNtpPeerIndexNext' object. If this is not the case, then the entry creation will fail.

atNtpPeerNameAddr.name: atNtpPeerNameAddr
atNtpPeerNameAddr.description: This object represents host name, or the IP address, of the NTP peer. This object is a current object for row creation. When a new row is created, this object is set with a default value '0.0.0.0', and the management application should change it to a desired value by a SET operation.

atNtpPeerMode.name: atNtpPeerMode
atNtpPeerMode.description: This object represents the mode of the peer. It's value is coded as follows: server(1), peer(2)

atNtpPeerPreference.name: atNtpPeerPreference
atNtpPeerPreference.description: This object specifies whether this peer is the preferred one over the others. It's value is encoded as follows: 0 - unknown 1 - not preferred 2 - preferred When the value of this object is 'not preferred', NTP chooses the peer with which to synchronize the time on the local system. If this object is set to 'preferred', NTP will choose the corresponding peer to synchronize the time with.

atNtpPeerVersion.name: atNtpPeerVersion
atNtpPeerVersion.description: This object represents the NTP version the peer supports. It's value is encoded as follows: 0 - unknown 1 - version 1 2 - version 2 3 - version 3 4 - version 4

atNtpPeerKeyNumber.name: atNtpPeerKeyNumber
atNtpPeerKeyNumber.description: This object represents the authentication key number.

atNtpPeerRowStatus.name: atNtpPeerRowStatus
atNtpPeerRowStatus.description: The status of this row. The reading of this object should have a value of 'active(1)'. For creation of new entry, a management application should set this object with value 'createAndGo(4)', and using the same value as that got from reading object 'atNtpPeerIndexNext', as the index for the new entry. When an entry is created, the object 'atNtpPeerNameAddr' in the entry is set with a default value '0.0.0.0'. The management application should change it to a desired value with a SET operation. The management application may need to take additional SET operations to set values for other objects, to ensure they have desired values. For deletion of entry, a management application should set this object with value 'destroy(6)'. Once an entry is deleted, other entries in the table which have bigger index than the deleted one, will be indexed again. Therefore a management application can effectively delete multiple entries by repeating the SET operation using the same index.

atNtpAssociationTable.name: atNtpAssociationTable
atNtpAssociationTable.description: This table contains NTP association information.

atNtpAssociationIndex.name: atNtpAssociationIndex
atNtpAssociationIndex.description: This object represents the index corresponding to a particular NTP association.

atNtpAssociationPeerAddr.name: atNtpAssociationPeerAddr
atNtpAssociationPeerAddr.description: This object represents the peer's IP address or host name.

atNtpAssocaitionStatus.name: atNtpAssocaitionStatus
atNtpAssocaitionStatus.description: This object indicates the association's status. It's value is defined as follows: master(synced), master(unsynced), selected, candidate, configured, unknown.

atNtpAssociationConfigured.name: atNtpAssociationConfigured
atNtpAssociationConfigured.description: This object indicates whether the association is from configuration or not. It's value can be either 'configured' or 'dynamic'.

atNtpAssociationRefClkAddr.name: atNtpAssociationRefClkAddr
atNtpAssociationRefClkAddr.description: This object indicates the IP address for the reference clock.

atNtpAssociationStratum.name: atNtpAssociationStratum
atNtpAssociationStratum.description: This object indicates the stratum of the peer clock.

atNtpAssociationPoll.name: atNtpAssociationPoll
atNtpAssociationPoll.description: This object indicates the time between NTP requests from the device to the server.

atNtpAssociationReach.name: atNtpAssociationReach
atNtpAssociationReach.description: This object indicates the reachability status of the peer.

atNtpAssociationDelay.name: atNtpAssociationDelay
atNtpAssociationDelay.description: This object indicates the round trip delay between the device and the server.

atNtpAssociationOffset.name: atNtpAssociationOffset
atNtpAssociationOffset.description: This object indicates the difference between the device clock and the server clock.

atNtpAssociationDisp.name: atNtpAssociationDisp
atNtpAssociationDisp.description: This object indicates the lowest measure of error associated with peer offset based on delay, in seconds.

atNtpSysClockSync.name: atNtpSysClockSync
atNtpSysClockSync.description: This object indicates whether the system clock is synchronized.

atNtpSysStratum.name: atNtpSysStratum
atNtpSysStratum.description: This object represents the stratum of the local clock.

atNtpSysReference.name: atNtpSysReference
atNtpSysReference.description: This object represents the current synchronization source.

atNtpSysFrequency.name: atNtpSysFrequency
atNtpSysFrequency.description: This object represents the actual clock frequency. source.

atNtpSysPrecision.name: atNtpSysPrecision
atNtpSysPrecision.description: Signed integer indicating the precision of the system clock, in seconds to the nearest power of two. The value is rounded to the next larger power of two; for instance, a 50-Hz(20 ms) or 60-Hz (16.67 ms) power-frequency clock would be assigned the value -5 (31.25 ms), while a 1000-Hz (1 ms) crystal-controlled clock would be assigned the value -9 (1.95 ms).

atNtpSysRefTime.name: atNtpSysRefTime
atNtpSysRefTime.description: This object indicates the local time when the local clock was last updated. If the local clock has never been synchronized, the value is zero

atNtpSysClkOffset.name: atNtpSysClkOffset
atNtpSysClkOffset.description: This object indicates the offset of the local clock relative to the server clock, in milliseconds.

atNtpSysRootDelay.name: atNtpSysRootDelay
atNtpSysRootDelay.description: This object indicats the total round-trip delay in milliseconds, to the primary reference source at the root of the synchronization subnet.

atNtpSysRootDisp.name: atNtpSysRootDisp
atNtpSysRootDisp.description: This object indicates the maximum error in milliseconds, relative to the primary reference source at the root of the synchronization subnet.
